Jonathan S. Halkyard  Chief Financial Officer, Extended Stay America, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships52$1,637,206As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Jonathan S. Halkyard has been the Chief Financial Officer of Extended Stay America, Inc. since January 05, 2015 and served as its Interim Chief Financial Officer since July 2014 until December 2014. Mr. Halkyard served as the Chief Operating Officer of Extended Stay America, Inc. since October 2013 to December 2014. Mr. Halkyard served as Assistant General Manager of Harrahs Entertainment Inc.'s Harveys Lake Tahoe from September 2001 to May 2002 and Assistant General ... Manager of Harrah's Las Vegas from May 2002 until November 2002. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at NV Energy, Inc, Nevada Power Company and Sierra Pacific Power Company from July 9, 2012 to September 13, 2013. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Caesars Entertainment Corporation from August 01, 2006 to May 30, 2012 and its Senior Vice President from July 2005 to December 2011, Executive Vice President from December 2011 to May 30, 2012, Treasurer from November 13, 2003 to July 2010 and Vice President of finance from November 2002 to July 2005. Mr. Halkyard joined Harrahs Entertainment Inc. as Director, Finance at Harrah's Lake Tahoe in 1999. He has been an Executive Director of London Clubs International Limited since November 13, 2006. Mr. Halkyard has been a Director of Dave & Buster's Inc since October 2011. He has been an Independent Director at Dave & Buster's Entertainment, Inc. since October 2011. He holds a BA from Colgate University and an MBA from Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




